    <p>The ex­hi­bi­tion is con­ceived as a cor­ri­dor of time that echoes the in­de­ter­mi­nate pas­sage of peo­ple’s days as they nav­i­gate through the global pan­demic and the de­struc­tion it leaves in its wake. Part of Pro­pos­als for Novel Ways of Be­ing, a new ini­tia­tive by the Sin­ga­pore Art Mu­seum and Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore as a col­lec­tive re­sponse by the vis­ual arts com­mu­nity to the pan­demic.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Sing­tel Spe­cial Ex­hi­bi­tion Gallery B, City Hall Wing, Level 3 Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore,</p>
    <p>1 St An­drew’s Road</p>
    <p>MRT: City Hall</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­day - Feb 21 next year AD­MIS­SION: Free for Sin­ga­pore­ans & per­ma­nent res­i­dents</p>
